A '''Hendanyn death mask''' was a ceremonial [[Death/Legends|death]] mask made by the [[Hendanyn]] that molded itself to its wearer's skin. The mask hid the signs of aging and would also store the memories of the wearer before he or she died, allowing the information to be retained after death and possibly passed on. The [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] [[Kueller]] wore one of these masks, [[Color/Legends|colored]] white with black accents with tiny jewels embedded in the corners of both [[Eye/Legends|eye]] slits.

==Behind the scenes==
''Star Wars'' author [[Abel G. Peña|Abel Peña]] wrote a passage for the ''[[Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide]]'' where it was stated that [[Darth Nihilus]]' [[Mask of Darth Nihilus|mask]] may have been a Hendanyn death mask.<ref name="tfn">{{JCFCite|url=posts/50677352|board=Literature|thread=Obscure Droids and Ewoks comics -- translated by Abel Peña|user=[[Abel G. Peña|Halagad_Ventor]]|date=2013-04-27|time=01:11 AM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171105191827/http://boards.theforce.net/threads/obscure-droids-and-ewoks-comics-translated-by-abel-peña.50010980/page-3}}</ref> However, this paragraph was ultimately cut.

